# Smart Greenhouse Architecture Rules

This project is a Spring Boot backend for a Smart Greenhouse System.

Use Java 17, Spring Boot, MongoDB, MQTT, MapStruct, Lombok and Gradle.

The architecture is Hexagonal Architecture + Vertical Slicing.

Package base:
com.proyectosu.invernadero

Follow the existing implemented slice:
prediction + actuator + greenhouse

This implemented flow is the official pattern:
Controller -> DtoMapper -> Command -> UseCase -> Domain Ports -> Infrastructure Adapters

Important rules:
- Do not put business logic in controllers.
- Controllers only receive requests, call mappers and execute use cases.
- Use MapStruct for DTO/request/response mapping.
- Use Lombok to reduce boilerplate.
- Domain models go in domain/model.
- Ports go in domain/port.
- UseCases go in application/usecases.
- Commands go in application/command.
- Inbound REST controllers go in infrastructure/inbound.
- Persistence documents, repositories, adapters and persistence mappers go in infrastructure/outbound.
- MongoDB is infrastructure.
- MQTT is centralized in shared.
- Use the existing MqttPublisherPort located in shared/domain/ports.
- Do not create duplicate MqttPublisherPort.
- Do not modify the existing working POST /api/predictions flow unless explicitly asked.
- Do not refactor authentication unless explicitly asked.
- Do not move existing packages unless explicitly asked.
- Do not invent unnecessary enterprise abstractions.
- Keep the project functional, clean, simple and maintainable.

When implementing new modules, copy the style of:
prediction
actuator
greenhouse

Use @Bean configuration for UseCases if the existing project does so.
Do not annotate UseCases with @Service unless the existing pattern changes intentionally.

For MongoDB:
- Use @Document for persistence documents.
- Use MongoRepository for repositories.
- Use MapStruct mappers for document/domain conversion.
- Adapters implement domain ports.

For MQTT:
- Listener should delegate to handlers.
- Handlers should not contain business logic.
- Handlers should convert MQTT payloads and call UseCases.